posed to be, a Russian cant term for “counterfeiter.” I am deeply indebted to Professor Stephen Jan Parker for suggesting a corresponding American underground slang word which delightfully glitters with the kingly gold dust of the Old Master’s name. Hitler’s grotesque and ferocious shadow was falling on Germany at the time I imagined those two brutes and my poor Romantovski.

The English translation appeared in Vogue, April, 1973.

V.N., A Russian Beauty and Other Stories, 1973





